---
// Canonical content-list wrapper. Pair with EditorialListItem.astro.
//
// Use for any list of dated/statused entries with a title and an optional
// blurb: writing index, /about career and projects, etc.
// Reading and wiki entries have richer per-item metadata (source lines,
// citation chips, mobile mono strips) and stay hand-rolled in their own
// pages — this component intentionally covers the simpler editorial
// pattern only.
//
// Spacing rationale: gap-6 reads well when items carry a blurb; if a list
// only has single-line items with no blurb, prefer the compact chrome list
// (e.g. /about Elsewhere) instead of dropping the gap on this one.
---
<ul class="not-prose flex flex-col gap-8 text-sm">
  <slot />
</ul>
